Quoted:  <br>
Theres a lot of bad, and misleading information going around about the entire thing here. <br>
<br>
Never, did I or anyone in AV threaten to wake the sleeper. That's not to say we've never discussed it amongst ourselves, but I'm sure harm has also. That is where I suspect this all started, as some ex-members who 'retired' but still had access to our boards, mysteriously appeared back online, in a different guild and then voila they are claiming we are going to wake the sleeper to slow them down or in retaliation. <br>
<br>
And Tums describes something that just isn't the case and it illustrates how little he knows about the entire situation. First of all, do you seriously think I give a damn whos killing telkorenar and gozzrem, dain or tormax, or yelinak for that matter. I'm sure this is news to everyone but, we either have 0 desire to kill these mobs, or they die out of our timezone and we haven't seen them in months. <br>
<br>
And, as bedrenken says, it is a general rule across servers, and yes including xev that you don't just walk in after someone else has killed aaryonar and just setup shop. AV didn't just make that up, we followed it, other guilds have followed it, because in the end its what is best for everyone. <br>
<br>
When concordance finally kills aaryonar, do you seriously want to camp for the night after a victory, only to find out that first an oceanic guild has gone in and cherry picked the front half of tov, and then later, a euro guild finishes it up. Then when you log on, tov is empty and you're left with your thumb up your ass. No, trust me thats not what you want wether you're able to put it all together or not. <br>
<br>
What I said that night to your officers had nothing to do with sleepers. They know how it works, I merely guided them to make the correct decision and leaving. Thats not to say I didn't make threats, merely to say that never have they involved sleepers. <br>
<br>
Now in another recent case, concordance for some reason told us they were going to kill nanzata. Theres a long standing agreement that is born out of respect that the other guilds that more actively are doing sleepers, leave nanzata up, so that if harm or av feel inclined to go kill him, they can do so without trying to find a time when there is another warder up and ventani. <br>
<br>
Of course concordance doesnt care about that, and we told them that wether nanzata is up or not wouldnt change our plans. That could be interpreted as a threat I suppose, but again, had 0 to do with concordance killing gozzrem, although really every time gozzrem dies, a piece of me dies too. <br>
<br>
Really, its about having an understanding and having some respect. While harm and av aren't best buddies, theres pretty much always been an understanding and some level of respect. I don't find myself having to say the things I've had to, to concordance leadership to any other guild on the server, in fact, you see us running to sleepers to wake up now that SM has done most of tov north? Nope, in fact, I answered questions about the zone, imagine that, getting help when you work with other guilds! <br>
